{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"caller":{"type":"direct"},"id":"toolu_014Yt4eW4dMrUTER6yqwgTJN","input":{"content":"---\nname: project-cledger-redaction-state\ndescription: conversation-ledger secret-redaction stack — what shipped (0.6.1/0.7.0), decisions made, and what's deferred\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nState of conversation-ledger's redaction work as of 2026-07-20.\n\n**Shipped:**\n- 0.6.1 — scan/sync finding reports fully mask the matched span (`<redacted>` + ~20 chars context + fingerprint, zero secret characters). Closes the sync-report channel of the capture/scan feedback loop.\n- 0.7.0 — opt-in `redact.knownSecrets` (default off). `cledger redact --pattern` remembers the exact scrubbed plaintext in `.git/conversation-ledger/known-secrets.json` (local, git-invisible, beside the allowlist); capture-time redaction then exact-matches those values out of every future draft under a `known-secret` rule id. Only `--pattern` feeds it (`--all` blanks whole content); sub-8-char values dropped. Enabled globally on this machine via `~/.config/cledger/config.json`.\n\n**Decisions (so the next agent doesn't re-litigate):**\n- The roadmap's original \"make capture-tier a strict superset of scan-tier\" framing was considered and **rejected** — promoting the deliberately-noisy scan rules to run at capture would silently rewrite innocent text, breaking the near-zero-false-positive invariant. The value-based learning above is the intended narrow form.\n- Store holds plaintext by necessity (fingerprints are one-way, can't drive exact matching); acceptable because `.git/` is as local-and-unshared as the transcripts, per the transport trust boundary.\n\n**Deferred, roughly by urgency:**\n1. Tighten the `keyword-assignment` scan rule — it fires on source identifiers (`secret: string`, `password:` keys); surfaced by dogfooding, this is what's producing most of this repo's ~93 benign findings.\n2. `chmod 0600` on known-secrets.json —