{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"caller":{"type":"direct"},"id":"toolu_01WbCj4m3j2vKJnzM88SvSZY","input":{"file_path":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger/README.md","new_string":"**Env-value masking** (opt-in, default off): Scrub exact values of environment variables and `.env` entries via `{\"redact\": {\"env\": true}}`.\n- Threat addressed: unstructured secrets in local config.\n- Cost of enabling: `.env` plain-config values get masked too; machine-dependent (rescans produce duplicate events with different ids).\n\n**Known-secret learning** (opt-in, default off): Remember the exact values a `cledger redact <event-id> --pattern` scrubbed, then exact-match them out of every future capture (under a `known-secret` rule id). Enable with `{\"redact\": {\"knownSecrets\": true}}`. Confirmed values are stored locally under `.git/conversation-ledger/known-secrets.json` — never tracked or pushed by git, the same tier as the allowlist. Only `--pattern` feeds it; values under 8 chars are never remembered.\n- Threat addressed: the capture/scan feedback loop — a value the broad sync scan catches but the conservative capture tier misses gets re-ingested raw every time you revisit it while fixing it. Once redacted, capture learns it and it can never be re-captured raw again.\n- Cost of enabling: confirmed secret plaintext lives in a new (local, unshared) file; like env masking, capture becomes machine-dependent for those values (another machine without the store captures the same line raw, under a different id).\n\n**Sync-time scan** (default on, tiered): Before any push, scans only new events with medium/high-precision rules (capture ruleset re-run, keyword assignments like `password=`, URL credentials). Findings abort the ledger push with a report and remediation instructions; the report shows ~20 chars of surrounding context with the matched value **fully masked** (`<redacted>`, zero secret characters) so the report itself can't re-seed the next scan. In the pre-push hook, a finding holds back only the ledger and lets your code push proceed unless `{\"transport\": {\"strict\": true}}`.","old_string":"**Env-value masking** (opt-in, default off): Scrub exact values of environment variables and `.env` entries via `{\"redact\": {\"env\": true}}`.\n- Threat addressed: unstructured secrets in local config.\n- Cost of enabling: `.env` plain-config values get masked too; machine-dependent (rescans produce duplicate events with different ids).\n\n**Sync-time scan** (default on, tiered): Before any push, scans only new events with medium/high-precision rules (capture ruleset re-run, keyword assignments like `password=`, URL credentials). Findings abort the ledger push with a report and remediation instructions; in the pre-push hook, a finding holds back only the ledger and lets your code push proceed unless `{\"transport\": {\"strict\": true}}`.","replace_all":false},"name":"Edit","type":"tool_use"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"39d040be1357efd96acceef66af15bf05ffbdb19","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:48648da3-5c2c-4827-96d5-7a6ed13224df","seq":417},"id":"ev1-625a8cf7f3fd14ade19f6fdc4fc4ba9662f11bccaf18bdd229f4229b478a1826","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-21T00:37:32.920Z","producer":{"session_id":"48648da3-5c2c-4827-96d5-7a6ed13224df","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.7.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","effort":"high","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"caller":{"type":"direct"},"id":"toolu_01WbCj4m3j2vKJnzM88SvSZY","input":{"file_path":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger/README.md","new_string":"**Env-value masking** (opt-in, default off): Scrub exact values of environment variables